  "event_preview": "The Streets of Arlington is a brand-new 2.73-mile (4.39 km) temporary street circuit in Arlington, Texas, weaving through the city's Entertainment District around AT&T Stadium and Globe Life Field — home of the Dallas Cowboys and Texas Rangers respectively. Designed by Tony Cottman, the circuit's 14 corners tie St. Petersburg for the most on any IndyCar street circuit, while its 0.900-mile main straightaway is the longest IndyCar will see on any street or road course — making it longer than any other IndyCar street circuit in the current calendar. The Java House Grand Prix of Arlington is the third race of the 2026 NTT IndyCar Series season and the inaugural running of the event, contested over 70 laps.",
